NOTE ON DATA LICENSING (not covered by the MIT license above):

This license covers the SOURCE CODE only. The biodiversity data the application
ingests and displays is owned by its providers and carries its own licenses —
several of them non-commercial (e.g. CC-BY-NC). This includes, among others,
GBIF occurrence records, the IUCN Red List, and iNaturalist media. Any
deployment that bundles or serves that data must honor each source's license
and attribution terms, which in practice restricts the assembled tool to
non-commercial, educational use. See the README for the source list.
